{"userId":"1897962947531485440","knowledgeAreaId":"Biology & Nature","characterId":"5","chatGroupCode":"8e04a5c5-67ff-4456-a296-0c381518ecab","coverUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/7f4add7e-ffda-4793-bfd2-cbb0dbc23e9d-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_01.png","bookTitle":"星空探秘","pageCount":"6","pages":[{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/7f4add7e-ffda-4793-bfd2-cbb0dbc23e9d-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_01.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/e5039974-96f4-491d-8556-bdb304135efc-audio_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_01.mp3","textContent":"夜幕降临，无数光点在深蓝色的天空中闪烁。Darwin站在自家的小院子里，仰望着满天繁星，眼中充满好奇。他伸出手，似乎想要触摸那些遥远的光点。其实，那些星星并不是我们看到的那么小，它们是巨大的天体，只因为距离地球非常遥远，才显得如此微小。许多星星比我们的太阳还要大许多倍，有些甚至是太阳体积的上百倍！Darwin拿出他的小望远镜，透过镜筒，那些原本只是点状的星星变得更加明亮，有些甚至呈现出不同的颜色——蓝色、红色、黄色，就像天空中的彩色宝石。","title":"夜空中的光点","pageNumber":0,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T14:15:33.043114"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/a7be2421-f40b-4494-ae1b-71ced342a98f-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_02.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/7c435c7e-75b1-45dd-98ba-1d73699c2818-audio_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_02.mp3","textContent":"浩瀚宇宙中，星云如彩色的云朵般漂浮。Darwin通过他的天文模拟器，观察着恒星的诞生过程。星星并非一直存在，它们也有自己的"生命周期"。每颗恒星都诞生于巨大的气体和尘埃云团——星云中。在引力作用下，这些物质逐渐聚集，形成一个越来越密集的核心。当核心温度和压力达到一定程度，氢原子开始融合成氦，释放出巨大的能量，一颗新星就此诞生。Darwin惊叹于这个过程，他看到模拟器中那团气体逐渐变得明亮，最终形成一个耀眼的光球，就像我们夜空中看到的星星一样。","title":"恒星的诞生","pageNumber":1,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T14:15:33.043114"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/286f45c1-6c29-4e40-ba92-fd90107b22ca-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_03.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/b1d27be4-5913-45fd-b89a-40c55b2ca64c-audio_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_03.mp3","textContent":"天文台的巨大显示屏上，展示着各种不同类型的恒星。Darwin站在显示屏前，认真记录着每种恒星的特点。原来星星并不都一样！它们有不同的大小、温度和颜色。最热的蓝色恒星表面温度可达30,000摄氏度以上，而较冷的红色恒星表面温度可能只有3,000摄氏度左右。我们的太阳是一颗黄矮星，表面温度约5,500摄氏度。除了温度不同，恒星的质量也各不相同。有些恒星质量是太阳的几十倍，而有些则只有太阳质量的一小部分。Darwin特别喜欢那些双星系统的图像，那里有两颗恒星围绕着共同的中心点旋转，就像宇宙中的舞者。","title":"恒星的种类","pageNumber":2,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T14:15:33.043114"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/51c6a4bb-c770-47a2-9cb4-20edb21a7337-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_04.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/067abcec-ed77-4b93-980b-56696f3cf80a-audio_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_04.mp3","textContent":"古老的星图铺展在桌面上，上面绘制着各种神话人物和动物的轮廓。Darwin用手指轻轻描绘着这些线条，它们连接着夜空中的星星，形成了我们熟知的星座。几千年来，人类一直观察星空，并将星星组合成各种图案，赋予它们故事和意义。北半球最著名的星座之一是大熊座，其中一部分星星组成了北斗七星。在南半球，南十字星则是航海者的重要导航标志。Darwin翻阅着不同文化的星图，发现同样的星星在不同文化中可能有完全不同的解释和故事。中国古代将星空分为二十八个星宿，而希腊神话中则有宙斯、赫拉等神明的故事映射在星座中。","title":"星座的故事","pageNumber":3,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T14:15:33.043114"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/0c75a944-0f1f-42aa-b99e-bedbcedce932-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_05.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/ce150b30-1fde-468d-a5b1-f427f14dcacd-audio_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_05.mp3","textContent":"宇宙的尺度模型前，Darwin显得异常渺小。这个模型展示了从地球到最近的恒星系统——半人马座阿尔法星的距离。即使光速如此之快（每秒30万公里），从那里到地球的光也需要4.3年的时间才能到达！这就是为什么天文学家用"光年"来测量宇宙距离，一光年是光在一年内传播的距离，约9.5万亿公里。当我们仰望星空时，我们看到的星光实际上是几年、几十年甚至几千年前发出的。Darwin意识到，观星就像是在看一部宇宙的历史纪录片。更令人惊讶的是，我们肉眼能看到的最远恒星距离地球约为2500光年，而整个银河系的直径则有10万光年之大！","title":"星星的距离","pageNumber":4,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T14:15:33.043114"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/9d6ef399-69dc-44c2-9d0b-2717127e05c9-image_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_06.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/84f70d73-22fe-4c96-ae58-8695b2bbf51a-audio_%E6%88%91%E5%B0%B1%E6%83%B3%E9%97%AE%E6%98%9F%E6%98%9F%E7%9A%84%E9%97%AE%E9%A2%98%E3%80%82_06.mp3","textContent":"夜空中，一道明亮的光线划过，转瞬即逝。Darwin迅速闭上眼睛，在心中默默许下一个愿望。人们常说看到流星可以许愿，但实际上，这些"流星"并不是真正的星星。它们是太空中的小碎片（陨石）进入地球大气层后，因摩擦而燃烧产生的光芒。大多数流星的体积很小，甚至如沙粒大小，但它们以极高的速度（每秒数十公里）穿越大气层，产生剧烈摩擦和高温，形成我们看到的光迹。每年都有特定时间的流星雨，如英仙座流星雨、双子座流星雨等，这是因为地球穿过某些彗星留下的碎片轨道。Darwin睁开眼睛，虽然知道科学真相，但他依然享受这许愿的美好时刻。

}
**title**: 星空探秘","title":"流星与许愿","pageNumber":5,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T14:15:33.043114"}],"imageValid":true}

{"userId":"1897962947531485440","knowledgeAreaId":"Geography","characterId":"1","chatGroupCode":"81a38f18-c3d6-4d34-8ee6-19987aff8411","coverUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/45eff418-eb1a-4fdd-a4d2-b2883bddd810-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_01.png","bookTitle":"Ocean's Temperature Rainbow Adventure","pageCount":"6","pages":[{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/45eff418-eb1a-4fdd-a4d2-b2883bddd810-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_01.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/0e120abf-ea4c-43c7-bd3e-ad2107618c44-audio_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_01.mp3","textContent":"The vast ocean stretched out like a giant blue blanket covering most of Earth. From above, it wasn't all the same color - some parts were deep blue while others appeared lighter or even greenish. Magellan stood on the deck of his research vessel, looking at a special map showing ocean temperatures with different colors. Red and orange areas marked warm waters, while blue and purple showed cooler regions. He wondered why the ocean wasn't the same temperature everywhere.","title":"The Colorful Ocean Map","pageNumber":0,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T18:29:59.339250"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/a8ab546e-1941-4446-8650-9db94c67efe9-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_02.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/5089a396-014f-4d2c-9747-637e97c66efc-audio_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_02.mp3","textContent":"The bright morning sun beamed down on the tropical waters. Sunlight penetrated the surface, warming the top layers of the ocean. Near the equator, where the sun shines most directly, the ocean absorbs more heat energy. Magellan dipped a temperature sensor into these warm equatorial waters, recording a reading of 82°F (28°C). He made notes about how the sun's position makes tropical oceans much warmer than waters near the North and South Poles, where sunlight hits at a slanted angle.","title":"Sunlight's Warming Touch","pageNumber":1,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T18:29:59.339250"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/658ce831-4ba7-4e72-a08a-4aecfb00bd17-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_03.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/315e476e-67c7-4600-bb8b-f6c5002ba987-audio_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_03.mp3","textContent":"Ocean currents flowed like massive rivers within the sea, moving warm and cold water around the planet. Magellan released a special floating device to track these powerful underwater movements. Some currents, like the Gulf Stream, carried warm tropical water toward the poles. Others, like the Labrador Current, pushed cold polar water toward the equator. These giant water highways helped spread heat around the world, creating areas where warm and cold waters meet and mix.","title":"Rivers of Water in the Sea","pageNumber":2,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T18:29:59.339250"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/49c90872-bef1-4b89-bd10-9c79f4cd8bbd-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_04.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/0caf720a-d03e-4303-889b-c2953bce826f-audio_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_04.mp3","textContent":"The ocean floor dropped away into darkness. Magellan lowered a deep-sea thermometer attached to a very long cable. As it descended, the temperature reading began to fall. Even in tropical areas, the deep ocean stayed cold - around 39°F (4°C). Unlike the surface waters warmed by sunlight, these deep waters remained chilly year-round. Magellan sketched a diagram showing how the ocean has layers of different temperatures, with warm water floating on top of colder, denser water below.","title":"Deep Ocean Mysteries","pageNumber":3,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T18:29:59.339250"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/93437821-b594-49ce-868e-700d5a4710dd-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_05.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/d37c8c46-ebd4-467c-a6e5-e29e89e01d37-audio_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_05.mp3","textContent":"Strong winds blew across the water's surface, creating white-capped waves. Magellan felt the cool breeze on his face as he watched the wind push the top layer of ocean water. This movement sometimes caused upwelling - where deep, cold water rises to replace surface water pushed away by wind. Near coastlines, this upwelling brought nutrient-rich cold water to the surface. Magellan observed how these areas often appeared as cool patches on his temperature map, even when surrounded by warmer waters.","title":"Winds and Waves at Work","pageNumber":4,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T18:29:59.339250"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/f70133e6-1c79-4e4c-9c14-b5066c8659fb-image_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_06.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/4d6080b7-4a18-4cd7-aacd-0abe581870d3-audio_1%3A%20Why%20do%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean%20have%20different%20temperatures%20than%20others%3F_06.mp3","textContent":"Schools of colorful fish darted through coral reefs in the warm waters. Magellan snorkeled above, observing how different sea creatures preferred specific temperature ranges. Tropical fish thrived in warm waters, while certain whales preferred cooler regions. Weather patterns also changed based on ocean temperatures - warm patches could fuel hurricanes, while temperature differences created fog and affected rainfall. Magellan realized that understanding ocean temperatures helps us predict weather, protect marine life, and even navigate safely across the seas.

}
**title**: Ocean's Temperature Rainbow Adventure","title":"Ocean Temperature's Big Impact","pageNumber":5,"createdAt":"2025-04-10T18:29:59.339250"}],"imageValid":true}

{"userId":"1897962948542976000","knowledgeAreaId":"Geography","characterId":"1","chatGroupCode":"413c4bed-572a-4eba-a73c-e0b06a452538","coverUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/270ca8e2-022f-45ac-9a04-572a03060de1-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_01.png","bookTitle":"七彩光魔法","pageCount":"6","pages":[{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/270ca8e2-022f-45ac-9a04-572a03060de1-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_01.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/dc895e1b-438e-4123-aa38-09c73e63779f-audio_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_01.mp3","textContent":"雨停了，天空中出现了一道美丽的彩虹。Leo站在窗前，眼睛睁得大大的。"哇！好漂亮的彩虹！"他兴奋地跳了起来。彩虹像一座七彩桥，红橙黄绿蓝靛紫，颜色真多呀！Leo拿起他的小望远镜，仔细地看着彩虹。彩虹为什么会出现呢？Leo决定去找答案。他穿上小雨靴，戴上帽子，准备出门探险。雨后的空气真新鲜，Leo深深地吸了一口气，开始了他的彩虹探索之旅。","title":"雨后彩虹","pageNumber":0,"createdAt":"2025-04-11T15:00:37.894871"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/40f7abb9-2d72-4943-9cbf-4c729bf69e90-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_02.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/12eb8bb6-3bc1-4094-94c6-fe8c3f92ac27-audio_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_02.mp3","textContent":"阳光照在花园里，地上的水坑闪闪发光。Leo蹲下来，看见一滴水珠挂在叶子上。阳光穿过水珠，地上出现了一点彩色光斑！Leo眨眨眼睛，惊奇地发现水珠就像一个小小的魔法球。他拿出妈妈给他的放大镜，对着水珠照去。哇！彩色的光更明显了！Leo明白了，水滴能把阳光分成不同的颜色。他想起科学书上说过，这叫"折射"。水滴就像一个小小的三棱镜，能把白光变成彩色光。","title":"水滴实验","pageNumber":1,"createdAt":"2025-04-11T15:00:37.894871"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/291d6778-7cdc-4f76-b7f8-bed8661adcb0-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_03.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/02759749-4659-4fe6-bd8a-56c980a298e0-audio_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_03.mp3","textContent":"花园里的喷水器开始工作了，水花四处飞溅。Leo跑到喷水器旁边，阳光透过水雾，形成了一道小彩虹！"太神奇了！"Leo高兴地转着圈。他用手指轻轻碰触水雾，彩虹却没有消失。Leo发现自己站的位置很重要，必须让阳光从背后照过来，才能看到彩虹。他移动位置，彩虹也跟着变化。有时候彩虹很亮，有时候又变淡了。Leo拍拍手，水珠飞舞，小彩虹在空中跳跃，真好玩！","title":"花园喷水","pageNumber":2,"createdAt":"2025-04-11T15:00:37.894871"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/2c5985f2-92ab-4465-b5d8-de29ba05d71a-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_04.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/4458ca8c-21b4-457a-b51b-c9ccd8307562-audio_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_04.mp3","textContent":"下午，Leo来到了图书馆。这里有好多科学书籍！他找到一本关于光的书，坐在明亮的窗边翻看。书上有彩色的图画，解释白光其实由七种颜色组成。Leo用手指跟着图画，学习光的旅行路线。白光进入水滴后，会弯曲并分开成不同颜色。红色弯得最少，紫色弯得最多，所以彩虹外圈是红色，内圈是紫色。Leo惊讶地张大嘴巴："原来彩虹的颜色顺序是有科学道理的！"他小心地记下这些知识，准备回家做实验。","title":"科学图书馆","pageNumber":3,"createdAt":"2025-04-11T15:00:37.894871"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/cee5a1bf-3f3d-45a5-9a2a-f97d074e8c3a-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_05.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/236ad212-fb9a-4466-9ff5-b5280ff0898e-audio_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_05.mp3","textContent":"回到家里，Leo决定自己制造彩虹。他拿来一个玻璃杯，倒满清水，放在阳光照射的窗台上。阳光穿过水杯，在墙上投出了一道小彩虹！Leo高兴得拍手跳跃："我成功啦！"他又拿来一面小镜子，放入水盆中，调整角度让阳光反射。哗！墙上又出现了彩虹！Leo发现，只要有水和阳光，就能创造彩虹。他用喷水壶对着阳光喷水，小水珠在空中飞舞，无数微小的彩虹在房间里闪烁，美丽极了！","title":"自制彩虹","pageNumber":4,"createdAt":"2025-04-11T15:00:37.894871"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/0ed59f0a-3521-490d-92df-88236ef0d14a-image_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_06.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/c1e536ce-2796-4b1a-9f0c-d1bac8c38751-audio_1%3A%20%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E9%98%B3%E5%85%89%E9%80%9A%E8%BF%87%E6%B0%B4%E9%9B%BE%E8%83%BD%E5%BD%A2%E6%88%90%E5%BD%A9%E8%99%B9%EF%BC%9F_06.mp3","textContent":"傍晚时分，Leo坐在院子里的小椅子上，看着天空中渐渐消失的彩虹。他现在知道了，彩虹是阳光通过水滴折射和反射形成的。每个小水滴都像一面小镜子，把阳光分成七种颜色。Leo拿出他的画本，画下今天学到的知识。他画了太阳、雨滴和彩虹，还用箭头标出光线的路径。Leo想：下次下雨后，我要告诉小朋友们寻找彩虹的秘诀！要站在太阳的对面，背对阳光，面向雨滴，就能看到美丽的彩虹啦！Leo合上画本，满足地笑了。

