{"userId":"1897962948702359540","knowledgeAreaId":"Biology & Nature","characterId":"5","chatGroupCode":"71bd0de2-60f6-40f5-ad56-214f4a9e4a0c","coverUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/b6f96e0c-1bba-47cb-8249-fd65da34d309-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_01.png","bookTitle":"The Egg-citing Life of Baby Chickens","pageCount":"6","pages":[{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/b6f96e0c-1bba-47cb-8249-fd65da34d309-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_01.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/29f81c1d-4256-400a-b781-079917e8f8d0-audio_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_01.mp3","textContent":"Long ago, before dinosaurs roamed the Earth, animals laid eggs in water. As time passed, some animals evolved to lay eggs on land. Chickens are birds that developed from these ancient creatures. Their eggs have hard shells that protect the growing baby inside, like a tiny house with walls and a roof. Inside this special house, everything a baby chicken needs to grow is already packed and ready.","title":"The Amazing Egg World","pageNumber":0,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T06:23:03.325446"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/f3ec7109-2a39-419a-8428-d74a1ab9c47c-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_02.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/77956b6c-23dd-414d-bb4e-95d083823f49-audio_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_02.mp3","textContent":"Deep inside a mother chicken's body is an amazing egg-making factory. This factory works every day to create eggs. First, a tiny cell called an ovum forms. Then, if this ovum meets special cells from a rooster, a baby chick can begin to grow. The mother chicken's body wraps this growing baby in layers of protection - first comes the yolk, then the egg white, and finally a hard calcium shell that forms just before the egg leaves her body.","title":"Inside the Egg Factory","pageNumber":1,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T06:23:03.325446"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/bebf8889-3520-472e-b793-6d3184c02367-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_03.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/3095f75e-aab4-4258-991b-1bdb8ad90dd8-audio_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_03.mp3","textContent":"The egg's shell is a marvel of nature's engineering. Made of calcium carbonate—the same material found in seashells and chalk—it's both strong and porous. Tiny holes in the shell, too small to see without a microscope, allow air to flow in and out. This helps the baby chick breathe as it grows. The shell also keeps germs out while holding moisture in. This perfect package allows chickens to lay their eggs on land instead of in water like fish do.","title":"The Protective Shell","pageNumber":2,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T06:23:03.325446"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/7614184c-02d9-4081-8624-afc2bb31bfb2-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_04.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/e04c6413-faae-4f48-b371-85cc68d75ebc-audio_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_04.mp3","textContent":"Inside the warm egg, an amazing transformation happens. The yolk provides rich food for the growing chick. The egg white offers protection and more nutrients. Day by day, the tiny heart begins to beat. Tiny wings, legs, and a beak form. The growing chick floats in a special fluid, much like how plants float in water. After about 21 days of development, the fully-formed chick is ready to meet the outside world.","title":"Growing Inside the Egg","pageNumber":3,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T06:23:03.325446"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/9ad4cda4-4f98-4716-a1b0-e1702d9b7984-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_05.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/3e61f6b4-4f05-488e-82bc-f2d40e1a693e-audio_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_05.mp3","textContent":"When the baby chick is fully formed, it needs to break out of its shell. The chick has a special tool for this job—a small, hard bump on its beak called an egg tooth. With this tool, the chick pecks at the shell from the inside. Tap, tap, tap! This hard work can take hours. Finally, cracks appear in the shell. The chick pushes and struggles until the shell breaks open. This amazing process is called hatching.","title":"The Great Hatching Day","pageNumber":4,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T06:23:03.325446"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/46ddc676-0faa-47e9-8d23-356abd1033bf-image_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_06.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/99216206-a576-48de-85fd-afb34aeba063-audio_Why%20do%20chickens%20have%20their%20babies%20through%20eggs%3F_06.mp3","textContent":"Chickens have their babies through eggs because this method offers many advantages. Eggs protect developing chicks from drying out on land. They provide all the food a growing chick needs. The hard shell keeps predators away. This egg-laying strategy is called being "oviparous" and is shared by birds, most reptiles, and some fish. Mammals like dogs and humans develop their babies inside their bodies instead. Each way of having babies helps different animals survive in their own special environments.

}
**title**: The Egg-citing Life of Baby Chickens","title":"Why Eggs Are Special","pageNumber":5,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T06:23:03.325446"}],"imageValid":true}

{"userId":"1897961945631885440","knowledgeAreaId":"Physics & Science","characterId":"7","chatGroupCode":"31fcc4fd-1ce7-4d8a-bb3c-4722584d8047","coverUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/5781b8da-1d2c-47ad-b0ba-fc65eeb7bdbc-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_01.png","bookTitle":"电的奇妙旅程","pageCount":"6","pages":[{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/5781b8da-1d2c-47ad-b0ba-fc65eeb7bdbc-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_01.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/641991bd-f9d0-444d-b863-c6107b228fa3-audio_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_01.mp3","textContent":"天空中乌云密布，一道明亮的闪电划破夜空。自然界中的电最早就是通过闪电被人们发现的。闪电是云层中正负电荷相遇产生的强大电流。Leo站在窗前，眼睛睁得大大的，看着窗外的闪电表演。他拿出一本科学书，里面解释说闪电是最原始的电力形式，温度可以达到摄氏三万度，比太阳表面还热五倍！这让Leo感到既害怕又好奇，他想知道人类是如何驯服这种强大的力量，把它变成可以点亮灯泡、让电视机工作的电能。","title":"闪电的力量","pageNumber":0,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T08:37:00.687570"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/8397a63c-295b-48a0-8b9a-65b0750e16ed-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_02.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/dbcfe9fb-52a6-43d3-bcb0-f966b3e6d9e5-audio_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_02.mp3","textContent":"阳光明媚的周末，一座巨大的水力发电厂矗立在河流旁边。高大的水坝控制着水流，让水有序地流向巨大的涡轮机。Leo戴着黄色安全帽，站在参观通道上，看着下方湍急的水流推动着巨大的涡轮。水流的力量让涡轮快速旋转，就像Leo玩的风车玩具，只是大了几百倍。这些旋转的涡轮连接着发电机，通过磁场和线圈的相互作用，把水的动能转变成了电能。Leo明白了，发电的秘密在于"运动"，只要能让涡轮转起来，就能产生电力。","title":"发电厂探秘","pageNumber":1,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T08:37:00.687570"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/f58b668b-3e2f-46c0-9a8a-59df4f11911c-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_03.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/6928dd9e-1e88-4756-9347-b17fdf400595-audio_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_03.mp3","textContent":"草原上，一排排巨大的风车迎风转动。风车的叶片在微风中轻轻摇摆，随着风力增强，转动得越来越快。Leo站在一台小型风力发电模型前，轻轻吹气，模型上的小灯泡立刻亮了起来。原来风也能变成电！不远处，一片闪闪发光的太阳能板朝向天空。阳光照射在这些特殊的板子上，里面的硅原子受到光子的撞击，释放出电子形成电流。Leo用手掌感受着太阳能板的温度，想象着阳光中的能量如何神奇地转变成电能。这些可再生能源不会用尽，是未来电力的重要来源。","title":"风力与阳光","pageNumber":2,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T08:37:00.687570"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/b9786d32-6f14-483a-84b6-5631a460149c-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_04.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/5a966b73-6e7f-4046-b5b3-e94d44669cb6-audio_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_04.mp3","textContent":"高高的电线杆连成一线，延伸到远方。这些是电力的高速公路，负责把发电厂的电输送到千家万户。Leo仰头看着这些电线，想象电流在里面快速流动的样子。电流其实是无数电子的移动，就像水管中流动的水一样。不过电流比水流快得多，几乎是光速的一半！电流从发电厂出发，经过变电站改变电压，通过输电线路传输，最后到达每个家庭的电表。Leo看着家里的电表，指针正在缓慢转动，记录着家里使用的电量。这个小小的盒子连接着整个城市的电网，让每个家庭都能使用电力。","title":"电的旅行","pageNumber":3,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T08:37:00.687570"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/4380fa24-95ee-45a1-a17e-db9b87e913ee-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_05.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/0e652416-c5bc-4beb-94b2-09a0524df35f-audio_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_05.mp3","textContent":"桌子上摆着各种形状的电池：圆柱形的、纽扣状的、方块状的。电池是便携式的电力来源，可以储存电能并在需要时释放。Leo小心地拿起一节干电池，观察它的正负极。电池内部有化学物质，通过化学反应产生电子流动，形成电流。这就像一个微型发电厂，随时准备提供电力。Leo拿出一个简易电路实验盒，把电池连接到电路上，小灯泡立刻亮了起来。他还学到了电池用完后不能随便丢弃，因为里面的化学物质可能污染环境，应该放到专门的回收箱里。","title":"电池的秘密","pageNumber":4,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T08:37:00.687570"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/e5aae3f7-93ff-4880-b00b-1e555c04abd6-image_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_06.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/df83d06e-99dd-470f-9a2e-d3b5fbdc4aaf-audio_%E4%BD%A0%E7%9F%A5%E9%81%93%E7%94%B5%E6%98%AF%E6%80%8E%E4%B9%88%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%84%E5%90%97%EF%BC%9F_06.mp3","textContent":"夜幕降临，城市的灯光渐渐亮起。Leo坐在书桌前，翻开一本关于未来能源的图画书。书中展示了许多新型发电方式：海浪发电、地热发电，甚至是利用细菌产生的生物电。科学家们正在研究如何让这些技术更高效、更环保。Leo想象着未来的电力系统：每个屋顶都有太阳能板，每个社区都有自己的小型发电站，电网变得更智能，可以根据需求自动调节。他拿出彩笔，在纸上画出自己设计的未来发电装置——一种结合风力和太阳能的新型发电机。通过了解电的来源，Leo对这种看不见摸不着却无处不在的能量有了全新的认识。

}

**title**: 电的奇妙旅程","title":"未来电力","pageNumber":5,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T08:37:00.687570"}],"imageValid":true}

{"userId":"1897962947531485440","knowledgeAreaId":"Geography","characterId":"1","chatGroupCode":"c739dcc1-7154-414d-88d5-5270ff4fec7d","coverUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/e0ecb51f-71f7-48f2-a5a1-55877d68090a-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_01.png","bookTitle":"地球大拼图","pageCount":"6","pages":[{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/e0ecb51f-71f7-48f2-a5a1-55877d68090a-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_01.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/7eaec8d2-b374-416a-bbfd-c772c238fa88-audio_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_01.mp3","textContent":"很久很久以前，地球刚刚形成。Leo站在科学博物馆的大屏幕前，眼睛睁得大大的。屏幕上，一个火红的小球慢慢变大。"哇！"Leo惊叹着。这个小球就是早期的地球，表面全是滚烫的岩浆，咕噜咕噜冒着泡泡。没有水，没有生命，只有热热的岩石和火山。Leo感觉自己的脸都被屏幕上的火光映红了。他伸出小手，好像要摸一摸那个炽热的小球。地球那时候真的好烫呀！","title":"地球的起源","pageNumber":0,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T13:22:52.644175"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/4855799a-84de-4eec-914e-dd655f0f1b74-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_02.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/180f40cf-bfe9-42da-b4d0-da9d85025c3f-audio_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_02.mp3","textContent":"地球慢慢冷却下来了。天空中，厚厚的云层聚集在一起。Leo站在窗前，看着外面下起了大雨。哗啦哗啦，雨点打在窗户上。"就像地球最早的雨水！"Leo兴奋地说。他用手指在窗户上画了一个大水滴。很久很久以前，地球也是这样下雨的。雨水从天上落下来，落呀落，一直下了几百万年。雨水慢慢积累，形成了小水坑，然后变成大水坑，最后变成了大海。Leo看着窗外的雨水，想象着它们汇成小溪，小溪流进大河，大河流进大海的样子。","title":"雨水的诞生","pageNumber":1,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T13:22:52.644175"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/4cb7705d-f789-461d-9311-73b0c7ebf873-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_03.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/b328da5f-0bd1-4468-b2ac-10f42f5f9e81-audio_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_03.mp3","textContent":"雨水越下越多，地球上出现了大片的水域。Leo坐在沙滩上，脚趾埋在温暖的沙子里。蓝蓝的海水在阳光下闪闪发光，哗啦哗啦拍打着岸边。"这么大的海洋是怎么来的呢？"Leo自言自语。他用小铲子挖了一个小坑，看着坑里慢慢渗出水来。地球上的水越来越多，低洼的地方都被水填满了。这些水汇集在一起，形成了大大小小的海洋。海水咸咸的，因为它溶解了岩石里的盐分。Leo舔了舔手指，尝到了一点点咸味，就像海水一样。","title":"海洋的形成","pageNumber":2,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T13:22:52.644175"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/8721cf35-7689-4025-ad15-640ba09f1329-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_04.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/f60072d1-bbd7-4d59-8948-c7f2924c5117-audio_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_04.mp3","textContent":"地球内部也在不停地活动。Leo趴在地上，感受着地面的坚实。他用小手拍了拍泥土，想象地下深处发生的事情。地球内部有热热的岩浆在流动，推动着地壳板块慢慢移动。有些地方被挤压得隆起来，形成了高高的山脉。Leo堆起一堆沙子，做成小山的形状。"这就是山脉隆起的样子！"他骄傲地说。有些地方则沉下去，形成了低洼的盆地。地壳的运动让地球表面变得高高低低，有的地方露出水面，成了陆地；有的地方低于水面，被海水覆盖。","title":"陆地的变化","pageNumber":3,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T13:22:52.644175"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/766a447e-3293-42c4-98c2-b26178522ba2-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_05.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/08359312-ec70-4ddc-bde1-a32ee134c97a-audio_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_05.mp3","textContent":"陆地和海洋的位置一直在变化。Leo站在高处，俯视着远处的山脉和海洋。风吹过他的头发，感觉真舒服。雨水冲刷着山石，把小石子带到低处。河流把泥沙带入海洋，堆积成新的陆地。Leo拿起水壶，往沙堆上倒了一点水，看着水流冲出小沟壑。"哇，好像小河流呀！"他惊叹道。同时，海浪也在不停地冲刷海岸，有时候会吞噬一些陆地。地球表面就这样，在风雨和海浪的作用下，不断地改变着形状。","title":"陆地与海洋的平衡","pageNumber":4,"createdAt":"2025-04-12T13:22:52.644175"},{"imageUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/a2d5b36e-92d0-4fa3-96c4-e82a25a82d28-image_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_06.png","audioUrl":"https://curio-app-dev.s3.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/upload/d468f844-c285-47f8-b4ea-392ca88568d5-audio_%E4%B8%BA%E4%BB%80%E4%B9%88%E5%9C%B0%E9%9D%A2%E4%BC%9A%E6%9C%89%E9%99%86%E5%9C%B0%E5%92%8C%E6%B5%B7%E6%B4%8B%EF%BC%9F_06.mp3","textContent":"经过几十亿年的变化，地球有了今天的样子。Leo坐在电脑前，看着地球的卫星图片。蓝色的海洋，绿色和棕色的陆地，白色的云朵，组成了一幅美丽的画面。"地球真漂亮！"Leo开心地说。现在，地球表面约有71%被水覆盖，形成了海洋；29%露出水面，成为了陆地。海洋和陆地相互依存，共同孕育了丰富的生命。Leo用手指轻轻描摹着屏幕上的海岸线，感叹大自然的神奇力量。地球上的陆地和海洋，就像一幅精心绘制的拼图，恰到好处地组合在一起。

